{
  "stem": "7458.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "In fact, it was called in Yiddish essen teg, which means 'to eat days.' And what it meant was that Yosel the student would be assigned Monday he would eat at Yankel's, and Tuesday he would eat at Schlaime's, and Wednesday he would eat at [INAUDIBLE], and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was called essen teg.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were established days when this yeshiva student would eat with a certain family.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And on the Shabbat we always had somebody at our house.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They served a function.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Aside from giving people a chance to be charitable, they also brought news from the outside world.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Remember, we had no radio and no newspapers and certainly no television.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the news had to travel through-- from mouth to mouth.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And those traveling scholars or travelling people who would end up in Jasionovka for the weekend, for the Shabbat, would bring news from the outside world as to what's going on.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They would also-- if they were scholars, they would test the children to see how much they know and how much they've learned.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was always a testing process going on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, as I earlier said, my father was not terribly religious by European standards.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Therefore, by the time I came around, there were many new movements and new winds were blowing through Eastern Europe.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Rather than being totally preoccupied with studying of the Torah and being religious and devoting your entire life to it, people begin to think about Zionism.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In fact, some of my sisters went to Zionist schools.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was also a socialist movement, the Bund.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I went to a Hebrew school called Beit Sefer Tarbut, which is a tarbut school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "However, I also studied Yiddish there and Polish and German, in that same school.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
